hopobject.body: Lost credit card rxdrugsaver.com "It's still economy, but you've got one or two fewer seats across on the wide jumbo jets and a little bit more recline," Lile says. "The service would be a little bit better, and it could be little bit quieter." However, the main allure of fourth class, according to Lile, is that since the fares are higher than coach (the price difference depends on the flight and airline), fourth-class passengers have a greater likelihood of getting upgraded to business class if desired.
